title: Get Your Mind Right!
features: "GET YOUR MIND RIGHT" is a 90 day guidebook that will unlock your potential and steer you towards your greatness. This book will make you accountable for your daily tasks for the next 90 days, while opening your mind and expanding your way of thinking. Throughout the book, there are stories of triumph, words of encouragement, and inspirational activities for you to complete. You were not created to be mediocre and it is time to recondition yourself to not only want to be great, but to expect to be great. There is no better time than now to turn your life around. GET YOUR MIND RIGHT!
description: Jarrell Liner is a native of Atlanta, GA. Jarrell's passion for helping people perform at their best stems from a life of pain, disappointments, and the acceptance of low expectations in his own life for years. No matter how bad things got in his life, Jarrell knew in his spirit that there was something more out there for not only himself, but for everyone around him. He refused to settle for second best and his determination eventually led him to persevere through his situations, overcome his obstacles, get rid of his excuses, and use his wisdom to become an accomplished business man. Today he is a business owner, motivational speaker, and life coach, using his testimony of triumph as a force to inspire and encourage people of all ages. His technique is to always pull directly from his experiences in life. He has been through many of the same personal, financial, and career challenges that his audiences have endured. Jarrell has "been there" and he consistently uses elements of his personal journey of pain, failure, and embarrassment to connect with people and motivate them to never give up and to reject excuses in their lives. Jarrell is passionate about making this world a better place by using his gift to encourage and uplift those that are in the same places that he has been in life. He is thankful for the chance to have come from where he came from and to be where he is. Jarrell understands that if you are blessed, it is your responsibility to reach out and bless others.
